         <abstract>
            <p>This paper (1) gives complete details of an algorithm to compute approximate kth roots; (2) uses this in an algorithm that, given an integer &lt;latex&gt;$n &gt; 1$&lt;/latex&gt;, either writes n as a perfect power or proves that n is not a perfect power; (3) proves, using Loxton's theorem on multiple linear forms in logarithms, that this perfect-power decomposition algorithm runs in time (log n)&lt;sup&gt;1+o(1)&lt;/sup&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
